Road safety is once again in the spotlight after 25 people died in a bus crash in the Eastern Cape. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The death toll from the gruesome bus accident in the Eastern Cape has been revised down from 29 to 25. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says the figure was caused by a miscommunication with the Frere Hospital. Several people were killed after the bus rolled down an embankment on Monday afternoon. READ: Eastern Cape bus crash death toll rises to 29 The driver is believed to have lost control of the bus that was transporting mainly pensioners and children. It's being reported the vehicle may have been overloaded and was speeding.